The paper presents a memory module for use in deep learning, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The use of deep neural networks and memory-augmented models suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses image classification and sequence-to-sequence models, which are relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language), respectively. The use of nearest-neighbor algorithms suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) may also be relevant. Finally, the focus on life-long and one-shot learning suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a likely sub-category.
